<li id="cite_note-5"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite class="citation pressrelease cs1"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://newsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org/ldsnewsroom/eng/background-information/temples">"Temples"</a>. <i>Newsroom</i> (Press release). <a href="/wiki/LDS_Church" class="mw-redirect" title="LDS Church">LDS Church</a>. 2012-09-17<span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2012-10-10</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Temples&amp;rft.pub=LDS+Church&amp;rft.date=2012-09-17&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fnewsroom.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fldsnewsroom%2Feng%2Fbackground-information%2Ftemples&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATemple+%28Latter+Day+Saints%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-6"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-6">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Recorded in the <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a>, Smith wrote that the Lord commanded the Saints to "establish a house, even a house of prayer, a house of fasting, a house of faith, a house of learning, a house of glory, a house of order, a house of God;" (see <a href="/wiki/Doctrine_and_Covenants" title="Doctrine and Covenants">Doctrine and Covenants</a> <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88?lang=eng&amp;id=119-120#p119">88:119&#8211;120</a>)</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Hinckley announced the use of smaller standardized temples in 1997 (<link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGordon_B._Hinckley" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Gordon B. Hinckley</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/general-conference/1997/10/some-thoughts-on-temples-retention-of-converts-and-missionary-service?lang=eng">"Some Thoughts on Temples, Retention of Converts, and Missionary Service"</a>. <i>167th Semiannual General Conference, October 1997</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2006-10-30</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=167th+Semiannual+General+Conference%2C+October+1997&amp;rft.atitle=Some+Thoughts+on+Temples%2C+Retention+of+Converts%2C+and+Missionary+Service&amp;rft.au=Gordon+B.+Hinckley&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fgeneral-conference%2F1997%2F10%2Fsome-thoughts-on-temples-retention-of-converts-and-missionary-service%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATemple+%28Latter+Day+Saints%29" class="Z3988"></span>). The base design is about 10,700 square feet (990&#160;m<sup>2</sup>), and temples built from the design are generally between 10,000 and 18,000 square feet (930 and 1,700&#160;m<sup>2</sup>). These temples generally do not include a large laundry facility, do not provide members with the ability to rent temple clothing, nor provide a cafeteria for members (Almanac, 2000).</span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-8">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFGordon_B._Hinckley" class="citation web cs1"><a href="/wiki/Gordon_B._Hinckley" title="Gordon B. Hinckley">Gordon B. Hinckley</a>. <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://www.churchofjesuschrist.org/study/general-conference/1998/04/new-temples-to-provide-crowning-blessings-of-the-gospel?lang=eng">"New Temples to Provide 'Crowning Blessings' of the Gospel"</a>. <i>168th Annual General Conference, April 1998</i><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">2006-10-30</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=168th+Annual+General+Conference%2C+April+1998&amp;rft.atitle=New+Temples+to+Provide+%27Crowning+Blessings%27+of+the+Gospel&amp;rft.au=Gordon+B.+Hinckley&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.churchofjesuschrist.org%2Fstudy%2Fgeneral-conference%2F1998%2F04%2Fnew-temples-to-provide-crowning-blessings-of-the-gospel%3Flang%3Deng&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATemple+%28Latter+Day+Saints%29" class="Z3988"></span></span>
</li>
<li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">A second meetinghouse exists in <a href="/wiki/Clitherall,_Minnesota" title="Clitherall, Minnesota">Clitherall, Minnesota</a>, but it is not currently in use.</span>
</li>
